Dar es Salaam is set to host Tanzania and China trade and investments forum on May, this year. According to Tanzania’s Embassy in China’s tweet, the event will be held in Tanzania’s business capital, thanks to the agreement reached in a meeting between the East African State Diplomat in China Mbelwa Kairuki and Yingke Law Firm representative Ms Nico Lang. The forum, the tweet says, will provide an opportunity for Tanzania and China company representatives to discuss various business-related issues including but not limited to Business-to- Business (B2B) in different sectors. “A trade and investments forum between Tanzania-China will be held in Dar es Salaam in May, this year. The forum will provide an opportunity for Tanzania and China companies to discuss the establishment of Business-to-Business (B2B) in different sectors,” reads the Embassy’s tweet.